To set up UART decoding on a Tektronix MSO4/5/6 Series oscilloscope, you typically need to:

1. Connect to the instrument.
2. Configure Channel 1 (CH1) as the UART input.
3. Set up the UART bus decode with the specified parameters: 115200 baud, 8 data bits, no parity, 1 stop bit (8N1).

Below is a TekAutomate Steps UI flow using only real step types and verified SCPI commands for Tek MSO4/5/6 Series. (Note: Actual UART decode setup uses the BUS subsystem.)

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "id": "connect_scope",
      "params": {
        "device_type": "SCOPE"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_ch1_coupling",
      "params": {
        "cmd": "CH1:COUP DC"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_ch1_bandwidth",
      "params": {
        "cmd": "CH1:BAND 500E6"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_ch1_scale",
      "params": {
        "cmd": "CH1:SCAle 500mV"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "bus_define_uart",
      "params": {
        "cmd": "BUS1:DEFINE UART,CHAN1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "bus_uart_baud",
      "params": {
        "cmd": "BUS1:UART:BAUD 115200"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "bus_uart_bits",
      "params": {
        "cmd": "BUS1:UART:DATA:WIDTH 8"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "bus_uart_parity",
      "params": {
        "cmd": "BUS1:UART:PARity NONE"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "bus_uart_stopbits",
      "params": {
        "cmd": "BUS1:UART:STOP 1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "id": "comment_uart_setup",
      "params": {
        "comment": "UART decode setup complete: CH1, 115200 baud, 8N1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "id": "disconnect_scope",
      "params": {}
    }
  ]
}
```

This flow connects to the scope, configures CH1, sets up UART decode on BUS1 with your specified parameters, and then disconnects. If you need to adjust channel scaling or other parameters, you can modify the relevant steps.

